Equine infectious anaemia, Poland
------------------
Information received on 17 Jun 2015 from Dr Krzysztof Jazdzewski, Deputy Chief Veterinary Officer, Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development, General Veterinary Inspectorate, VARSOVIE, Poland.
Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 31 May 2015
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 12 Jun 2015
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 1960
Manifestation of disease: sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: Equine infectious anaemia virus
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Krakow, Krakow, Krakowski, Malopolske
Date of start of the outbreak: 31 May 2015
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 14 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Equidae / 7.14 / 0 / 0 / 0
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: control of vectors; quarantine; movement control inside the country; no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
National Veterinary Research Institute (national laboratory) / Equidae / agar-gel precipitation (AGP) test / 12 Jun 2015 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

